criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patients ≥18 years scheduled to undergo FOB (as determined by their medical care
             team) who are immunocompromised (active hematologic malignancy or post hematopoietic
             stem cell transplant), and are hypoxic with pulmonary infiltrates. Hypoxia will be
             defined as requiring supplemental low flow oxygen ≥ 2L/min by nasal cannula to
             maintain SpO2 >90%.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. requiring supplemental oxygen > 8L/min by nasal cannula;

          2. receiving HFNC before randomization;

          3. nasal deformity or packing precluding HFNC use;

          4. hypercapnia (PaCO2 > 60) or respiratory acidosis (pH <7.25);

          5. requiring NIV for over 1 hour or intubated.
